LU-CIX in P&amp;T Solutions|publisher=Pt.lu|accessdate=2015-04-02}}&lt;/ref&gt; In 2012, LIX, the neutral Internet exchange operated by the RESTENA Foundation, merged with LU-CIX.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.lix.lu |title=Merger between LIX and LU-CIX|publisher=Lix.lu|accessdate=2015-04-02}}&lt;/ref&gt; In March 2013, LU-CIX launched the 'Central European Peering Hub' in order to provide the opportunity to its members to connect to other IXs' reseller programs, AMS-IX (Amsterdam), LINX (London), DE-CIX (Frankfurt) and France-IX (Paris), etc.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.lu-cix.lu/downloads/press-release-central-european-peering-hub-29-03-2013.pdf |title=LU-CIX and IX Reach Open up Connectivity to Major Internet Exchanges|publisher=Lu-cix.lu|accessdate=2015-04-02}}&lt;/ref&gt;
